Privacy Policy
‍
Last Updated: October 12, 2024
MINDMUSH
, owned by Kramer Ventures GmbH and based in Switzerland, is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our mobile games and services. By using our games, you agree to the collection and use of information as outlined below.
‍
1. Information We Collect
‍
When you use our mobile games and services, we may collect the following types of information:
‍
a. Non-Personal Information
We collect non-personal information, including:
Device information (e.g., type, operating system, IP address).
Game usage data (e.g., levels completed, in-game purchases).
General user behavior and interaction within the game.
This information is used to improve our services and enhance your gaming experience.
‍
2. Third-Party Services
We use third-party services to improve your experience and facilitate key features within our games:
‍
a. App Stores
For in-app purchases, we use Apple App Store and Google Play Store. These platforms process transactions and manage payment information.
b. AppLovin
We utilize AppLovin for ad mediation to deliver personalized ads within the game.
c. Tapjoy
We use Tapjoy for offerwalls, which provide opportunities to earn in-game rewards through interacting with ads.
‍
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
Provide and maintain our games and services.
Personalize in-game content and advertisements.
Improve game performance and user experience.
Process in-app purchases through app stores.
Offer rewards through Tapjoy’s offerwalls.
‍
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share non-personal information with third-party service providers like AppLovin, Tapjoy, and app stores to facilitate ads, game performance analytics, and in-app purchases.
‍
5. Data Security
We implement appropriate measures to protect the information we collect. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your data.
‍
6. Children’s Privacy
Our services are not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take steps to remove the data.
‍
7. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your data, such as the right to access, correct, or delete your information. If you wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at the address provided below.
‍
8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices. Significant updates will be posted within the game or on our website. Please check this policy periodically for updates.
‍
9. Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
MINDMUSH (Kramer Ventures GmbH)
Address
: Hagenholzstrasse 81, 8050 Zürich, Switzerland
Email
:
contact@mindmush.com
By using our games and services, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
